        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The main goal of this paper is to investigate the electric resistance of a layered phthalocyanine and palladium (Pc + Pd) structure under the inffuence of various hydrogen concentrations in nitrogen and air. We show that during the interaction of hydrogen with bilayer structures metal-free phthalocyanine and palladium there occurs a strong change in the resistance of these structures. This would correspond to an acousto-electric effect in the SAW sensor system",
